The first biological limitation of our model comes from the purely diffusive behavior imposed on each edge of the graph. It would be biologically relevant to incorporate some kind of directed or ballistic motion (drift term in (2.2)) given that many individuals set off on transportation lines travel from one specific city to another preferentially, see Bertaglia and Pareschi (2021) for a purely hyperbolic model. This would result in an equation on each edge of the form\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
